Package: semFromKeys
Type: Package
Title: Run Structural Equation lavaan Models from Keys Lists
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Timothy F.", "Bainbridge",
      email = "tfbainbridge@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Specifying lavaan models manually can be time consuming when
    multiple similar models are required. The semFromKeys package aims to
    streamline the process of running lavaan models by generating model code
    from simple keys lists instead of writing out model code manually.
    - cfa.from.keys() runs a separate confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) for
    each list item.
    - bifactor.from.keys() runs a separate bifactor model for each item from a
    list of general factors.
    - efa.from.keys() runs a exploratory factor analyis (EFA) model with a
    rotation targeted based on a keys list.
    - esem.from.keys() runs exploratory structural equation models (ESEM)
    where an item or latent variable is regressed on a set of EFA factors.
    
    The package is early in its development so if something breaks or does not
    work as intended, please let me know on the github page.
